
Overview of noun notice

The noun notice has 7 senses (first 6 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (8) notice -- (an announcement containing information about an event; "you didn't give me enough notice"; "an obituary notice"; "a notice of sale)
2. (3) notice, observation, observance -- (the act of noticing or paying attention; "he escaped the notice of the police")
3. (2) notification, notice -- (a request for payment; "the notification stated the grace period and the penalties for defaulting")
4. (1) notice -- (advance notification (usually written) of the intention to withdraw from an arrangement of contract; "we received a notice to vacate the premises"; "he gave notice two months before he moved")
5. (1) poster, posting, placard, notice, bill, card -- (a sign posted in a public place as an advertisement; "a poster advertised the coming attractions")
6. (1) notice -- (polite or favorable attention; "his hard work soon attracted the teacher's notice")
7. notice -- (a short critical review; "the play received good notices")

Overview of verb notice

The verb notice has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (39) detect, observe, find, discover, notice -- (discover or determine the existence, presence, or fact of; "She detected high levels of lead in her drinking water"; "We found traces of lead in the paint")
2. (19) notice, mark, note -- (notice or perceive; "She noted that someone was following her"; "mark my words")
3. (1) comment, notice, remark, point out -- (make or write a comment on; "he commented the paper of his colleague")
4. notice, acknowledge -- (express recognition of the presence or existence of, or acquaintance with; "He never acknowledges his colleagues when they run into him in the hallway"; "She acknowledged his complement with a smile"; "it is important to acknowledge the work of others in one's own writing")
